Note using the change-of-base formula that $\log_y x \log_x y = 1$. We find that \begin{align*}
(\log_y x)^2 + (\log_x y)^2 &= (\log_y x)^2 + 2\log_y x \log_x y + (\log_x y)^2 - 2\log_y x \log_x y \\
&= (\log_y x + \log_x y)^2 - 2\log_y x \log_x y \\
&= 7^2 - 2 \\
&= \boxed{47}.
\end{align*}

question:
Find the number of ordered triples $(x,y,z)$ of real numbers such that
\begin{align*}
x + 2y + 4z &= 12, \\
xy + 2xz + 4yz &= 22, \\
xyz &= 6.
\end{align*}

The equation of the hyperbola shown below can be written as
\[\frac{(x - h)^2}{a^2} - \frac{(y - k)^2}{b^2} = 1.\]Find $h + k + a + b.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.3 cm);

